crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This code defines a command-line interface for a "forge" operation. It configures arguments for creating digital certificates. The process allows using an existing CA certificate (PFX) with its password or generating a self-signed root CA if none is provided. Users can specify various parameters for the new certificate, including Subject Alternative Names (UPN, DNS, SID), the certificate's Subject, issuer, serial number, application policies, and key size. It also supports cloning properties from a template certificate. The resulting certificate and its private key are saved to a specified output PFX file, which can be password-protected. The core certificate forging logic is delegated to an external module (`certipy.commands.forge`).
